    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Art and design that focuses narrowly on the marketing of products and other sales, including typography, layout, packages, mailings, and other visual materials having to do primarily or exclusively with sales. It may include design for the Internet and social media.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000075711/Hymers and Sharpe, Technique and Practice of Advertising Art (1940)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kunst en ontwerp uitsluitend gericht op productmarketing en andere vormen van verkoop, inclusief typografie, lay-out, verpakkingen, mailings en andere visuele materialen die vooral of uitsluitend voor verkoopdoeleinden zijn gemaakt. Ook ontwerp voor het internet en sociale media kan hieronder vallen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
